text.section:
A legislative body may authorize the planning director or another designee to grant an administrative adjustment from the following requirements in a zoning law enacted by the legislative body:
height;
setback;
bulk;
parking;
loading, dimensional, or area; or
similar requirements.

Procedures for administrative adjustments may address:
applications;
notice to the public and to the parties in interest;
an opportunity for a public hearing;
an opportunity for the taking of testimony and evidence; and
decision making.
